1 9. “User” means an individual who accesses or uses a social
2 media platform.
3 B. 1. A social media platform shall perform reasonable age
4 verification methods to determine whether a user who is a resident
5 of this state is a minor. A social media company shall segregate
6 any personal information gathered specifically for reasonable age
7 verification purposes and shall not use the personal information for
8 any other purpose except those provided in subparagraphs a through f
9 of paragraph 2 of subsection D of this section.
10 2. If a user is determined to be a minor, a social media
11 platform shall:
12 a. set default privacy settings to prioritize maximum
13 privacy of such minor user’s account, including
14 settings that:
15 (1) restrict the visibility of the minor user’s
16 account to only connected accounts,
17 (2) limit the minor user’s ability to share content
18 to only connected accounts,
19 (3) restrict any data collection and sale of data
20 from a minor user’s account that is not otherwise
21 required for core functioning of the social media
22 platform,
23 (4) disable search engine indexing of the minor
24 user’s profiles,
